The paper discusses a source-to-source compiler for real-valued programs with error specifications, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and programming languages (cs.PL). The focus on safety-critical applications suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions handling unbounded loops, which is a topic in logic and verification (cs.LO). Finally, the title "Towards A Compiler For Reals" suggests a connection to computer architecture (cs.AR) and the implementation of numerical computations.
